        <section class="faq-section" id="faq">
            <div class="section-container">
                <div class="section-header reveal">
                    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                    <p>Common questions about our legal services</p>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-grid-simple">
                    <!-- FAQ Item 1 -->
                    <div class="faq-box reveal" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                        <div class="faq-box-question" itemprop="name">How do I choose the best lawyer in Karachi for my case?</div>
                        <div class="faq-box-answer" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                            <p itemprop="text">To choose the best lawyer in Karachi, verify their enrollment with the Sindh Bar Council, confirm they are an Advocate High Court for complex matters, check their specialization in your specific case type (civil, family, criminal), review their track record and success rate, and ensure their office location provides convenient access to relevant courts. Always request an initial consultation to assess communication and comfort level.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
                    <div class="faq-box reveal" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                        <div class="faq-box-question" itemprop="name">What are the legal fees for hiring a lawyer in Karachi?</div>
                        <div class="faq-box-answer" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                            <p itemprop="text">Legal fees in Karachi vary by case complexity and lawyer experience. Initial consultations typically range from PKR 5,000-15,000. Family law cases cost PKR 50,000-300,000, civil litigation PKR 70,000-500,000, property disputes PKR 100,000-400,000, and criminal defense PKR 70,000-500,000. Corporate matters typically work on retainer basis. MR Law Associates offers transparent milestone-based billing with the initial consultation fee credited toward your retainer.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
                    <div class="faq-box reveal" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                        <div class="faq-box-question" itemprop="name">Can a lawyer in Karachi help with property disputes and stay orders?</div>
                        <div class="faq-box-answer" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                            <p itemprop="text">Yes, a property lawyer in Karachi can file for stay orders under Order 39 Rule 1 & 2 CPC of the Civil Procedure Code to prevent illegal dispossession. They can handle illegal possession cases under the Illegal Dispossession Act 2005, file suits for declaration to establish title, pursue partition suits for inheritance matters, and represent you in Sindh High Court for property-related constitutional petitions. Emergency stay orders can often be obtained within 24-48 hours.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
                    <div class="faq-box reveal" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                        <div class="faq-box-question" itemprop="name">How long does a civil case take in Karachi courts?</div>
                        <div class="faq-box-answer" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                            <p itemprop="text">The duration of civil cases in Karachi varies by complexity. Simple recovery suits may resolve in 6-12 months, while complex property disputes can take 2-4 years. Cases involving multiple parties or requiring extensive evidence take longer. Interim relief like stay orders can be obtained quickly (24-72 hours). Our proximity to City Court allows for efficient case management and faster filing of urgent applications.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- FAQ Item 5 -->
                    <div class="faq-box reveal" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                        <div class="faq-box-question" itemprop="name">Should I hire a female lawyer for family law matters?</div>
                        <div class="faq-box-answer" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                            <p itemprop="text">Many women in Pakistan feel more comfortable discussing sensitive family matters with a female lawyer. Advocate Reema Jawed provides culturally appropriate representation while ensuring your legal rights are fully protected in divorce, khula, child custody, and maintenance cases. Her female-led practice offers a safe environment for clients to discuss personal issues.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- FAQ Item 6 -->
                    <div class="faq-box reveal" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                        <div class="faq-box-question" itemprop="name">Can I get bail immediately after arrest in Karachi?</div>
                        <div class="faq-box-answer" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                            <p itemprop="text">Bail availability depends on the offense type. For bailable offenses, bail is a right and can be obtained the same day. For non-bailable offenses, the court considers factors like offense severity, evidence strength, and flight risk. MR Law Associates provides 24/7 emergency bail services with same-day court appearances for urgent matters.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- FAQ Item 7 -->
                    <div class="faq-box reveal" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                        <div class="faq-box-question" itemprop="name">Can overseas Pakistanis hire a lawyer in Karachi without visiting?</div>
                        <div class="faq-box-answer" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                            <p itemprop="text">Yes, overseas Pakistanis can hire a lawyer in Karachi remotely. You need to execute a Special Power of Attorney (SPA) attested at the Pakistani Embassy/Consulate in your country of residence. This document is then verified and registered in Pakistan. Your appointed lawyer can then handle property matters, divorce proceedings, inheritance cases, and litigation on your behalf without requiring your physical presence in Karachi.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- FAQ Item 8 -->
                    <div class="faq-box reveal" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                        <div class="faq-box-question" itemprop="name">What should I do if an FIR is registered against me?</div>
                        <div class="faq-box-answer" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                            <p itemprop="text">If an FIR is registered against you, immediately contact a criminal defense lawyer before speaking to police. Do not sign any documents without legal counsel present. Your lawyer can file for pre-arrest bail if needed, challenge the FIR's validity, and guide you through the investigation process. Early legal intervention is crucial for protecting your rights.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
